{
  "doc_id": "48530",
  "text": "QICs are frequently used within Europe, the United States, Canada and Australia and are generally acknowledged for their success [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Despite their widespread use, the actual effectiveness of QICs is still in question [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Because learning is central to the QIC, more insight into the learning process within a QIC may help to understand how we can improve the effectiveness of QICs. Little research has yet been conducted into if, and how, learning takes place in a QIC [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] and how QICs facilitate the learning processes of their participants [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . To understand more about how learning can be enhanced in a QIC it is necessary to gain more insight into how individual participants learn.",
